UNIT 1 â€“ Introduction to Security and Risk Management
Unit Overview

This unit introduced core definitions of security and risk management and outlined the fundamental concepts of threats, vulnerabilities, and the risk management process. It established the distinction between qualitative and quantitative risk assessment approaches and highlighted the role of standards in managing risk effectively.

Artefacts

Summary of risk definitions

Discussion post on fairness and accountability risks

Wiki contribution (risk terminology)

Reflection

This unit provided a foundational understanding of how risk is conceptualised and managed in information systems. I learned that risk is not solely about probability but also about uncertainty, impact, and context. The distinction between qualitative and quantitative assessments clarified why many organisations adopt hybrid approaches when data is limited. This learning shaped my later work by ensuring that all subsequent risk assessments were grounded in structured, standards-based processes rather than intuition.

References

Aven, T. and Thekdi, S. (2025). Risk Science. Routledge.

NIST (2002). SP 800-30 Risk Management Guide.
